[DOCUMENT]
TITLE: MIL-STD-498 OCD (Operational Concept Document)

[SECTION]
TITLE: 1. Scope

[SECTION]
TITLE: 1.1 Identification

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: OCD-001
TITLE: Document Identification
STATEMENT: This document shall be identified as the Operational Concept Document (OCD) for the Satellite Communication Management System (SCMS) project.
RATIONALE: Proper document identification ensures traceability and configuration management.

[/SECTION]

[SECTION]
TITLE: 1.2 System overview

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: OCD-002
TITLE: System Overview
STATEMENT: The Satellite Communication Management System (SCMS) shall provide comprehensive management and control of satellite communication networks, including real-time monitoring, automated routing, and security management.
RATIONALE: A clear system overview establishes the foundation for all subsequent operational concepts and requirements.

[/SECTION]

[SECTION]
TITLE: 1.3 Document overview

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: OCD-003
TITLE: Document Structure
STATEMENT: This document shall be organized into seven major sections covering scope, referenced documents, current system analysis, change justification, new system concept, operational scenarios, and impact summary.
RATIONALE: Structured document organization facilitates understanding and review by stakeholders.

[/SECTION]

[/SECTION]

[SECTION]
TITLE: 2. Referenced documents

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: OCD-004
TITLE: Reference Standards
STATEMENT: The system shall comply with MIL-STD-498, IEEE 830, and ISO/IEC 25010 standards for software requirements and quality characteristics.
RATIONALE: Compliance with established standards ensures system quality and interoperability.

[/SECTION]

[SECTION]
TITLE: 3. Current system or situation

[SECTION]
TITLE: 3.1 Background, objectives, and scope

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: OCD-005
TITLE: Current System Background
STATEMENT: The current satellite communication infrastructure consists of legacy systems with manual configuration management, limited real-time monitoring capabilities, and fragmented security controls across multiple platforms.
RATIONALE: Understanding current system limitations provides context for improvement requirements.

[/SECTION]

[SECTION]
TITLE: 3.2 Operational policies and constraints

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: OCD-006
TITLE: Operational Constraints
STATEMENT: The system shall operate within Department of Defense (DoD) security policies, International Telecommunication Union (ITU) regulations, and Federal Communications Commission (FCC) spectrum allocation requirements.
RATIONALE: Regulatory compliance is essential for satellite communication systems.

[/SECTION]

[SECTION]
TITLE: 3.3 Description of current system or situation

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: OCD-007
TITLE: Current System Description
STATEMENT: The existing system comprises three separate satellite networks with independent control systems, manual handoff procedures, and limited cross-network coordination capabilities.
RATIONALE: Detailed current system description identifies specific areas for improvement.

[/SECTION]

[SECTION]
TITLE: 3.4 Users or involved personnel

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: OCD-008
TITLE: User Community
STATEMENT: The system shall support satellite network operators, communication engineers, security analysts, and system administrators across multiple military and civilian organizations.
RATIONALE: Understanding user roles and responsibilities is critical for system design.

[/SECTION]

[SECTION]
TITLE: 3.5 Support concept

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: OCD-009
TITLE: Current Support Concept
STATEMENT: The current support concept relies on on-site technical personnel with specialized training on legacy systems, requiring 24/7 staffing at multiple locations.
RATIONALE: Current support limitations drive requirements for improved automation and remote management.

[/SECTION]

[/SECTION]

[SECTION]
TITLE: 4. Justification for and nature of changes

[SECTION]
TITLE: 4.1 Justification for change

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: OCD-010
TITLE: Change Justification
STATEMENT: The current system limitations in automation, security, and cross-network coordination justify the development of an integrated Satellite Communication Management System.
RATIONALE: Clear justification ensures stakeholder buy-in and resource allocation.

[/SECTION]

[SECTION]
TITLE: 4.2 Description of needed changes

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: OCD-011
TITLE: Required Changes
STATEMENT: The system shall implement automated network management, unified security controls, real-time monitoring and alerting, and integrated cross-network coordination capabilities.
RATIONALE: Specific change requirements guide system design and implementation.

[/SECTION]

[SECTION]
TITLE: 4.3 Priorities among the changes

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: OCD-012
TITLE: Change Priorities
STATEMENT: Security enhancements shall have the highest priority, followed by automation improvements, monitoring capabilities, and cross-network coordination features.
RATIONALE: Prioritization ensures critical capabilities are delivered first.

[/SECTION]

[SECTION]
TITLE: 4.4 Changes considered but not included

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: OCD-013
TITLE: Excluded Changes
STATEMENT: Changes not included in this scope include complete replacement of existing satellite hardware, modification of orbital parameters, and integration with non-military communication systems.
RATIONALE: Scope boundaries prevent project creep and maintain focus on achievable objectives.

[/SECTION]

[SECTION]
TITLE: 4.5 Assumptions and constraints

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: OCD-014
TITLE: System Assumptions
STATEMENT: The system assumes continued availability of existing satellite infrastructure, stable regulatory environment, and availability of qualified personnel for system operation and maintenance.
RATIONALE: Documented assumptions provide context for system design decisions.

[/SECTION]

[/SECTION]

[SECTION]
TITLE: 5. Concept for a new or modified system

[SECTION]
TITLE: 5.1 Background, objectives, and scope

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: OCD-015
TITLE: New System Objectives
STATEMENT: The new system shall provide unified management of satellite communication networks with enhanced security, automation, and monitoring capabilities while maintaining backward compatibility with existing infrastructure.
RATIONALE: Clear objectives guide system design and evaluation criteria.

[/SECTION]

[SECTION]
TITLE: 5.2 Operational policies and constraints

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: OCD-016
TITLE: New System Policies
STATEMENT: The new system shall implement role-based access control, automated security monitoring, and compliance with DoD cybersecurity requirements while maintaining operational flexibility.
RATIONALE: Operational policies ensure system security and regulatory compliance.

[/SECTION]

[SECTION]
TITLE: 5.3 Description of the new or modified system

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: OCD-017
TITLE: New System Architecture
STATEMENT: The new system shall implement a distributed architecture with centralized management, redundant control centers, automated failover capabilities, and secure communication protocols.
RATIONALE: Robust architecture ensures system reliability and scalability.

[/SECTION]

[SECTION]
TITLE: 5.4 Users/affected personnel

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: OCD-018
TITLE: New User Roles
STATEMENT: The new system shall support enhanced roles including system administrators, security analysts, network operators, and automated monitoring systems with appropriate access controls.
RATIONALE: Defined user roles ensure proper system access and accountability.

[/SECTION]

[SECTION]
TITLE: 5.5 Support concept

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: OCD-019
TITLE: New Support Concept
STATEMENT: The new system shall implement remote monitoring and management capabilities, automated diagnostics, predictive maintenance, and reduced dependency on on-site technical personnel.
RATIONALE: Improved support concept reduces operational costs and improves system availability.

[/SECTION]

[/SECTION]

[SECTION]
TITLE: 6. Operational scenarios

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: OCD-020
TITLE: Normal Operations
STATEMENT: During normal operations, the system shall automatically monitor satellite network health, manage traffic routing, and provide real-time status updates to authorized users.
RATIONALE: Normal operational scenarios define baseline system behavior.

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: OCD-021
TITLE: Emergency Operations
STATEMENT: During emergency operations, the system shall automatically implement priority routing, activate backup communication channels, and provide enhanced monitoring and alerting capabilities.
RATIONALE: Emergency scenarios ensure system reliability under critical conditions.

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: OCD-022
TITLE: Maintenance Operations
STATEMENT: During maintenance operations, the system shall support graceful degradation, automated failover to backup systems, and coordinated maintenance scheduling across multiple networks.
RATIONALE: Maintenance scenarios ensure system availability during planned downtime.

[/SECTION]

[SECTION]
TITLE: 7. Summary of impacts

[SECTION]
TITLE: 7.1 Operational impacts

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: OCD-023
TITLE: Operational Impact Assessment
STATEMENT: The new system shall improve operational efficiency by 40%, reduce manual intervention requirements by 60%, and enhance security posture through automated monitoring and response capabilities.
RATIONALE: Quantified impacts justify system investment and guide performance expectations.

[/SECTION]

[/SECTION]
